  "Inner (core) electrons create a 'shield' of negative charge between the nucleus and outer electrons. This repulsion partially cancels the nuclear attraction, so valence electrons feel less pull.": "",
  "As shielding increases, valence electrons are:": "",
  "Destroyed": "",
  "Harder to remove": "",
