  "Slater's rules assign different shielding values based on electron positions: same-shell electrons shield ~0.35, n-1 shell shields ~0.85, and deeper shells shield ~1.0 each. This gives more accurate Zeff than the simple Z-S calculation.": "",
  "What is penetration in the context of shielding?": "",
